The paper deals with image aesthetics and proposes a model that can not only give an aesthetic score for an image but also generate a textual description explaining why the image leads to a plausible rating score. This involves tasks related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed model is based on neural networks and involves multi-task learning, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves the use of a dataset containing images and comments, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
